  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nWith the current `Ownable{2Step}` contracts, users can either transfer ownership in one step or two steps. There is currently no implementation to have both options in one contract. However, this would make sense for, e.g., a contract factory setup. First, the factory deploys a contract, thereby inheriting the ownership. Second, the factory transfers the ownership to an EOA in one step. Going forward, the EOA can transfer the ownership in two steps.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nWithin the `Ownable2Step` contract, instead of overriding the `transferOwnership` function to be a two-step transfer, extend the `Ownable` contract with a `transferClaimableOwnership` function that enables the two-step transfer, while keeping `transferOwnership` as a one-step transfer.",
