    "body": "Hello @Artifex1 \r\n\r\nThis is something we discussed for a long time in the `Ownable2Step` issue/PR.\r\n\r\nIt was decided that in `Ownable2Step`, the `transferOwnership` should be overridden so that the default is a 2 step transfer.\r\nThere was a discussion about including, or not, the one step transfer using another function (something like `forceTransferOwnership`). This was not done because it would be opinionated from us to include it by default when anyone can enable this manually in their code.\r\n\r\nYou may want to do\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract MyOwnable is Ownable2Step {\r\n    function forceTransferOwnership(address newOwner) public onlyOwner() {\r\n        _transferOwnership(newOwner);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```\r\ncontract MyOwnable is Ownable2Step {\r\n    function transferOwnership(address newOwner) public override onlyOwner() {\r\n        _transferOwnership(newOwner);\r\n    }\r\n    function transferClaimableOwnership(address newOwner) public onlyOwner() {\r\n        super.transferOwnership(newOwner);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
